parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause various issues, such as faulty brake lights, faulty airbag system, and faulty engine control system, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function properly
the airbag system fails to deploy
the electrical accessories do not function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brake lights do not function properly
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Exhaust System and Catalytic Converter
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked exhaust system and catalytic converter can cause carbon monoxide poisoning, loss of power, and decreased performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving on highways.
The failure of the crankshaft and camshaft sensors can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty restarting.
The failure of the air mass sensor can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and decreased performance.
The excessive oil consumption and engine failure can cause engine damage, loss of power, and decreased performance.
The transmission failure can cause loss of power, decreased performance, and accidents.
The sudden acceleration can cause accidents, loss of control, and damage to the vehicle.
The airbag failure can cause injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: injury or death in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected activation of the brakes can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The brakes engage suddenly without driver input
the vehicle jerks or pulls to one side
and the vehicle may come to a stop or lose speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause complete loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
The failure of the yaw rate sensor can cause the electronic stability program (ESP) to malfunction, leading to sudden and unexpected brake activation, loss of control, and accidents.
symptoms: the brakes engage suddenly without driver input
and the vehicle may jerk or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS/ESP system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: the brakes engage suddenly without driver input
and the vehicle may jerk or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of brake fluid can cause complete loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
